The tiger (scientific name: Panthera tigris; also known as the tiger, although it is more often used for animals of the species Panthera pardus and its subspecies) is an animal belonging to the phylum Chordata, subphylum vertebrates, class mammals, meat eaters (carnivores), family felidae (cats). ), genus Panthera, and belongs to the species Tigris.
